According to the Risk Analysis Division of the Political Capital Division, the activities of the Hungarian Guard, formed in August of this year with the support of the Movement for a Better Hungary, have increased from a number of points of view the political risk of Hungary and the region.
The company's "risk warning" is written: in relation to the activities of the Hungarian Guard, the greatest political risk is that "with the worsening of the ethnic tensions between the Roma and non-Gypsies of Hungary, even in the short term, violent ethnic confrontations can occur".
The main reason for this is that the political strategy of the Hungarian Guard is probably the provocation of such an event - added the representative of the research institute.
They said that all of this was due to one of the main flaws of Hungarian political life's protagonists: "The public life protagonists gave the public debate of the Gypsy problem to representatives of the radical and extremist political groups, who were able to base their political strategy on the existing differences between Roma and Hungarians."
This exacerbates the problem, makes normal dialogue impossible, strengthens extremists and increases the likelihood of the outbreak of violent conflicts - they estimate.
Moreover, according to the National Guard's research institute, as a result of the high attention of the national and international media, "the image of Hungary abroad has deteriorated significantly, especially with regard to the stability and democratic development of the country".
They remind us that: since the fall of 2006, it has received increasing publicity and impetus to the reorganization of the radical and extremely right-wing groups of Hungary and that since the summer of 2007, numerous organizations have been formed in the country that are self-defined by “national self-defence associations”.
