Like the alleged homosexuality or mental disability of certain victims of deportation.
The records of the concentration camps or detention orders established by the Gestapo had been gathered after war for a practical purpose: to find those deported or subjected to compulsory work and, if necessary, to provide proof of their detention, in order to open the way for compensation.
Still today in Bad Arolsen, more than 300 permanent employees deal with tens of thousands of individual requests.
