Congress approves the Mifid transposition, which entered into force on 1 November.
In parallel with its parliamentary procedure, which ended today with the Congress vote on the amendments incorporated into the draft in the Senate, the Government has submitted to the public hearing the rules that will develop the new law, with the aim of both of them entering into force before the end of the year.
The representatives of the different groups agreed to highlight the efforts made by Members and Senators to negotiate and consensus the best rules in order to ensure the protection of investors and to regulate in detail the business of entities for the efficient functioning of markets.
The Mifid, which amends the Securities Market Act, involves the modernisation of financial markets, while strengthening investor protection, improving the supervisory powers of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and fostering cooperation between the various European Union supervisors.
The new regulation will enable financial advisory services to be provided to both specialized firms and to natural or legal persons and creates a new type of financial services signatures (ESIS), financial advisory companies (FIAs), which are associated with securities companies, securities agencies and portfolio management companies.
In addition, it expands the number of financial instrument operations systems, so that regulated secondary markets are combined with multilateral trading systems and order internalization systems, which will compete with current stock exchange managers.
The Act also obliges investment service companies to disclose information on the key aspects of their business profile, risk exposure and risk management forms on the market and requires them to keep a record of all their operations in order to facilitate supervision by the CNMV.
A number of amendments were incorporated by the Committee on the Economy of Congress in its footsteps, including the fact that the subordinated debt is regarded as a "complex" financial instrument given its high risk to the investor, which has been demonstrated with the United States high-risk mortgage debt (subprime).
In addition, the transposition of the directive was used to legally delimit the functions that could be performed by graduates in Economics and Entrepreneurships 30 years after the real decree delimiting the professional functions reserved for economists was adopted in 1977.
The Senate, for its part, incorporated the creation of new figures in the financial sector, such as that of the mediator, who will work abroad, will not require the authorisation of the CNMV and will be able to provide its product marketing and customer capture services to various investment firms at the same time.
